A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 1 of Title 6 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general
2 provisions relative to aviation, so as to provide the Department of Transportation with
3 authority over vertiports; to provide for definitions; to amend Code Section 48-13-50.2 of the
4 Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to definitions relative to excise tax on rooms,
5 lodgings, and accommodations, so as to revise the definition of the term "tourism product
6 development" to include air service product expansion at air carrier airports; to provide for
7 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 Chapter 1 of Title 6 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to general provisions
11 relative to aviation, is amended by revising Code Section 6-1-1, relating to powers and duties
12 of Department of Transportation â€” Aviation and aviation facilities generally, as follows:
13 "6-1-1.
14 (a) As used in this title, the term:
15 (1) 'Landing field' shall include a vertiport.
