16 (2) 'Vertiport' means an area specifically designated and primarily used for the landing,
17 takeoff, and servicing of aircraft with a maximum takeoff weight of greater than 1,320
18 pounds that is capable of vertical takeoff and landing.
19 (b) The Department of Transportation shall have the following powers and duties:
20 (1) To plan for and establish a long-term policy in regard to the establishment,
21 development, and maintenance of aviation, landing fields, and aviation facilities in the
22 this state;
23 (2) To promote and encourage the use of aviation facilities of the state for air commerce
24 in the this state and between the state, other states, and foreign countries;
25 (3) To cooperate, counsel, and advise with the State Transportation Board in regard to
26 the planning, construction, development, and maintenance of airports, landing fields, and
27 air navigation facilities in the this state;
28 (4) To cooperate, counsel, and advise with municipalities and other political subdivisions
29 of the state and with other departments, boards, bureaus, commissions, agencies, or
30 establishments, whether federal, state, or local, or public or private, for the purpose of
31 promoting and obtaining coordination in the planning for and in the establishment of
32 development, maintenance, and protection of a system of air routes, airports, landing
33 fields, and other aviation facilities in the this state."
34 SECTION 2.
35 Code Section 48-13-50.2 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to definitions
36 relative to excise tax on rooms, lodgings, and accommodations, is amended in paragraph (6)
37 by striking "or" at the end of subparagraph (O), by replacing the period with "; and" at the
38 end of subparagraph (P), and by adding a new subparagraph to read as follows:
39 "(Q) Air service product expansion at air carrier airports."
